    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-vad-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 factors under ASME V&V 40 at Model Risk Level 5 for the Class III VAD COU. While multiple factors show achieved levels below required levels — most notably model form (achieved 2, required 4) and numerical code verification (achieved 3, required 4) — the team determined that the Monte Carlo UQ results bound the hemolysis predictions conservatively below the absolute clinical threshold with 95% confidence, providing sufficient assurance for the intended regulatory submission. The package is accepted under the Minimal conformance profile. NOTE: Digital signature is pending completion of the organizational PKI provisioning workflow; the sha256 hash is provided to support pre-signature integrity tracking. The signature field will be populated and the profile upgraded to ProfileComplete upon PKI provisioning.",
